terary texts, including The Fairie Queene and The Tempest, and sources such as sermons, dictionaries, and visual artifacts, to navigate alliances between traditional semantics and post-colonial political criticism. Beautifully written and deeply engaging, Colonial Virtue also models an expansive methodology for literary studies through its close readings and rhetorical analyses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and societyzGreat BritainzColoniesxHistory. 0aTemperancexColonieszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aTemperancezEnglandxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269642640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442696426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442696426.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK